race.comment: KATE'S TIARA (7) stuck on well last start to finish third over 1200m at Scone after showing good early speed. Hard to beat in this suitable race. HAIKU STAR (9) has built nicely into this and is hitting his straps now fourth-up. Loves this distance and is sure to be very competitive. DIS IS HEAVEN (3) improved last time out to score after being prominent at the bend over 1000m at Kempsey. Tougher this time but is open to further improvement and is drawn perfectly. Don't take lightly. HELLCIBELL (5) returns and is a noted performer. Struggled to make an impact last prep but this is an easier assignment and she gets in well with the claim. No reason she can't play a major role first-up. JACK BE LUCKY (1) tackles tougher opposition this time but is a distance specialist worth respecting.
